+
+### Verified direct-route boundary
+
+Alfred may route directly only to verified direct route targets. Non-verified specialists route through `meta_ops` unless later validated by the seed layer or a governed routing update.
+
+### Daily Command Board boundary
+
+The Daily Command Board is a planning and recommendation surface. It may classify and recommend daily craft-flow placement, but it must not silently mutate SSOT, OpState, calendar, canonical KB, or an operator-locked board.
+
+### Trace, state, and pattern boundary
+
+Session Export remains trace. OpState changes remain delta candidates until accepted. Pattern observations remain candidate-first until threshold evidence and promotion rules are satisfied.
 